---
import { Img } from "astro-imagetools/components";
---

<html>
  <head
    ><meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Nunito:wght@300;500&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="cover">
      <Img
        src="/src/assets/images/aero.png"
        alt=""
        loading="lazy"
        placeholder="blurred"
        format="webp"
        breakpoints={[400, 800, 1200, 1600, 2000]}
        quality={50}
      />
      <Img
        src="/src/assets/images/aero_before.jpg"
        alt=""
        loading="lazy"
        placeholder="blurred"
        format="webp"
        breakpoints={[400, 800, 1200, 1600, 2000]}
        quality={50}
        attributes={{
          img: {
            id: "topImage",
          },
        }}
      />
      <div id="coverMain">
        <h1>Aero<br /><span id="byline">by Blake</span></h1>
        <h2>
          Virtual wind tunnel.<br />For your garage.<br />By webcam.
        </h2>
        <a class="button" href="/aero/app">Launch App</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <h3>Expand your Indoor Cycling Training Arsenal</h3>
    <p>
      On the road, finding and utilizing an optimal cycling body position
      significantly reduces the defeating effects of wind resistance - a
      cyclist's worst enemy at speed. Finding and practicing this positioning
      means spending hundreds of hours on the road, or if the budget allows,
      comissioning your closest wind tunnel. Today, <span class="italics"
        >Aero</span
      > will navigate you towards wind resistance minimization - from the web.
    </p><p>
      <span class="italics">Aero</span> enables interactive experiementation of your
      body geometry as you pedal along at home. Finally picture these invisible effects
      in vivid color. Improve your power efficiency in a way power meters themselves
      can't. Bring your webcam. That's all.
    </p>
    <h3>Academic Design & Cutting-Edge Innovation</h3>
    <p>
      Hi, I'm <a href="/" target="_blank">Blake</a>. In graduate school, I
      studied and further advanced state-of-the-art Machine Learning methods.
      Driving this passion was (and still is) a strong desire to quantitatively
      model real-world use cases and apply computational insight.
    </p><p>
      As I continue along my endurance triathlon journey, I'm learning to
      harmoniously and compoundingly leverage my complete skillset - swimming,
      biking, and running, but also Machine Learning, Physics, Mathematics, and
      Programming.
    </p>
    <p>
      <span class="italics">Aero</span> blew me back into top research journals,
      where I brushed up on computer vision-based image segmentation, fluid dynamics,
      Eulerian simulation, and hardware-accelerated web technologies. Culminating
      from a thorough academic survey, chaotic whiteboard sessions, curious software
      experiments, and key development victories, I share this tool with the cycling
      community.
    </p>
  </body>

  <style lang="scss" is:global>
    * {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      box-sizing: border-box;
      font-family: Nunito, sans-serif;
      line-height: 150%;
      font-weight: 300;
    }
    body {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      padding-bottom: 100px;
    }
    body :not(#cover, #cover *) {
      max-width: 800px;
    }
    .italics {
      font-style: italic;
    }
    #cover {
      position: relative;
      width: 100%;
      height: calc(100vh - 100px);
      height: calc(100svh - 100px);
      margin-bottom: 1em;
    }

    img {
      position: absolute;
      height: 100% !important;
      object-fit: cover;
      z-index: -1;
    }
    @keyframes fadeout {
      0% {
        opacity: 1;
      }
      100% {
        opacity: 0;
      }
    }

    @keyframes fadeInBackground {
      from {
        background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
      }
      to {
        background-color: transparent;
      }
    }

    #topImage {
      animation: fadeout 4s ease-in-out infinite alternate both;
    }

    #coverMain {
      position: absolute;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    h1 {
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      text-align: left;
      color: white;
      // animation: fadeInBackground 4s ease-in-out infinite alternate both;
      font-size: 3.3em;
      line-height: 0.4em;
      padding: 0.4em 0.7em;
      padding-top: 0.7em;
      font-style: italic;
      // filter: saturate(0) contrast(30000%);
      #byline {
        font-style: normal;
        font-size: 0.3em;
      }
      font-weight: 500;
      // border-bottom-right-radius: 0.2em;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 2.6em;
      text-align: center;
      align-self: center;
      color: white;
      font-weight: 500;
      padding: 0 1em;
    }

    .button {
      color: white !important;
      text-decoration: none !important;
      backdrop-filter: blur(0.5em);
      background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
      border: 1px solid white;
      box-shadow: 0 0 2em 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
      padding: 0.5em 0.8em;
      font-size: 1.2em;
      margin-top: 1em;
      border-radius: 0.4em;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    h3 {
      font-size: 1.5em;
      margin: 0.5em 1.5em;
      margin-top: 1em;
      text-align: center;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    p {
      font-size: 1.2em;
      margin: 0.4em 1.5em;
      text-indent: 2em;
      a {
        color: rgb(30, 127, 255) !important;
        text-decoration: underline;
      }
    }

    @media screen and (max-width: 500px) {
      h2 {
        font-size: 2em;
      }
    }
  </style>
</html>
